<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
(taken from 
<bibRefCitation author="Marsh, PM" journalOrPublisher="Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute" pageId="436" pageNumber="437" title="The Doryctinae of Costa Rica (excluding the genus Heterospilus)." volume="70" year="2002">Marsh 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Cyclostome braconids with circular or oval mouth opening formed by concave apical margin of clypeus, mandibles (when closed) and concave labrum; occipital carina usually present, rarely absent; fore tibia with row or (rarely) cluster of stout, short spines along anterior edge distinct from regular setae; epicnemial carina present; double node at apex of dorsal valve of the ovipositor; flange at the apico-lateral corner of the propleuron just above the fore coxa and extending slightly over ventro-lateral corner of pronotum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Species now included in the 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Doryctinae">Doryctinae</taxonomicName>
were first described by Linnaeus and Fabricius in the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Ichneumon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ichneumon" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ichneumon</taxonomicName>
. Many of these species and subsequently described new species were transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Bracon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bracon" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Bracon</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius, JC" journalOrPublisher="Reichard" pageId="436" pageNumber="437" title="Systema Piezatorum." year="1804">Fabricius (1804)</bibRefCitation>
. In 1808, Spinola separated from this genus what he called the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Bracon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bracon petiolatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petiolatus">Bracon petiolatus</taxonomicName>
group which was later described as the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Spathius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Spathius" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Spathius</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nees ab Esenbeck, CG" journalOrPublisher="Nova Acta Academiae Caesoreae Lepoldino-Carolinae" pageId="436" pageNumber="437" pagination="299 - 310" title="Appendix ad J. L. C. Gravenhorst conspectum generum et familiarum Ichneumonidum, genera et familiam Ichneumonidum abscitorum exhibens." volume="9" year="1818">Nees (1818)</bibRefCitation>
. This is apparently the first genus to be later included in the 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Doryctinae">Doryctinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Foerster, in his monumental study of braconid classification, divided the 
<taxonomicName family="Braconidae" lsidName="" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="family">Braconidae</taxonomicName>
into several groups which later became subfamilies, tribes and subtribes (
<bibRefCitation author="Foerster, A" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlingen des Naturhistorischen Vereines der Pruessischen Rheinlande und Westphalens" pageId="436" pageNumber="437" pagination="226 - 288" title="Synopsis der Familien und Gattungen der Braconiden." volume="19" year="1862">Foerster 1862</bibRefCitation>
). He included doryctine genera in groups he called 
<taxonomicName family="Doryctoidae" lsidName="" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="family">Doryctoidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName family="Euspathioidae" lsidName="" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="family">Euspathioidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName family="Hecaboloidae" lsidName="" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="family">Hecaboloidae</taxonomicName>
. Forester was the first to use the name 
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Doryctinae">Doryctinae</taxonomicName>
(-oidae) and is considered the author of the subfamily name.
</paragraph>
